data.title: Exclusive dining in a restored 1890's house
data.text: An old house has been restored to it's original period, and is a small restaurant. A fixed menu is offered, with a choice of four entrees (picked ahead of time). The food was all very good, and the service nice.

data.title: Girls Luncheon
data.text: This place is wonderful. The chicken salad and quiche was wonderful! Owner friendly and shared his history and how he ended up in St Joseph, Mo. He was knowledgable about the history of the beautiful old house. It was a private setting for old friends to reconnect.

data.title: Eight for Dinner
data.text: One of the most delightful evenings I've known.  The surroundings are sumptious & Jim shared his stories with us of preserving & restoring this spectacular home.  He is a delight & clearly very talented.  We are all preservationists with historic homes of our own & we gave it an "A+"

data.title: Saint Joseph jewel
data.text: Incredible food and service nestled in beautiful historic home!  Perfectly prepared salmon, accompanied by roasted potatoes and greens was followed by a trio of delicious desserts. Our beverage - ice tea with a hint of raspberry - was included with the meal, as was dessert.  Like having a private chef, baker and staff, we were catered to by the very cordial owners with our choice of entrees. All this at lunch- and I can't wait to visit again for dinner or a special occasion!  Prior  reservations required.

data.title: One of a kind - Fantastic
data.text: I love to go to local one of a kind restaurants and this was one of the reasons. Celebration of 26 years with my partner.  The private dining experience for the value was perfect. Jim served us at our pace.  We enjoyed salmon and the chicken Marsala.  Desert was perfect trio mix of chocolate, seasonal pumpkin and a beautiful cupcake.  Jim uncorked our wine and off we went.  Absolutely Fabulous.

data.title: Best meal I've ever had!!!
data.text:
It is hard to put into words the dinning experience at the JC Wyatt house. It's as if you step into your own Victorian Home and greeted by your own butler and chef preparing your favorite meal. The decor is stunning, the appetizers delectable, filet outstandingly savory and the desserts are divine. 

It will be dreaming of this dining experience for a long time.

data.title: Attention to detail - unmatched anywhere!
data.text: This is a one of a kind experience at a very affordable price.  The food is delicious and very generous in portion.  The service is excellent. The presentation was pretty enough to be in a magazine and the atmosphere was like stepping back in time and every detail being perfect.  The decor is some of the best I've seen.  I can't think of anything that would have made it any better.  Truly, it was one of the best experiences I've had while dining out.

data.title: Wonderful lunch
data.text: I met a girlfriend for lunch here two weeks ago.  The food was superb.  I had the shrimp kabob with couscous.  The desserts were to die for...excellent service, great ambience. In would highly recommend this place.  I am looking forward to returning again for lunch and dinner as well!

data.title: Excellent food and service. .
data.text: Jeff and Jim are wonderful hosts. House is full of antiques and always decorated especially during during holidays.Food and service are excellent. Been there for lunches and dinners. One  of my groups has annual Christmas  lunch there.

data.title: Don't miss this exceptional Fine Dining experience
data.text: Dining here is by reservation only and well worth your time and planning. The atmosphere in this historic home is charming, the top-notch service is welcoming and personal and the exceptional quality and taste of the food is prepared by a trained chef (who is also one of the owners). We will definitely return this quite little romantic spot. What a great find!

data.title: Exceeding all expectations
data.text: If you live in St Joe you know this is not the mecca for remarkable food,  But wait it does exist.  Don't expect to just drop in as you must make your reservation days in advance and order your main course when you do,  Well worth the wait as everything is  made fresh with all the flourishes you find in some of the best NY city establishments,  Although a limited menu it offers well balanced choices.  Come enjoy some of best food  you may ever have and you didn't have to go to Kansas City.

data.title: Awesome
data.text: The food was spectacular and the owners are wonderful to deal with.  Beautiful old home with great food.  One of the best places in St Joseph to eat!

data.title: What a treat in St. Joseph!!   Don't miss out on this gem!
data.text: We visited for the first time last November for my birthday and it was a fantastic experience!   Food was amazing, service was exceptional and even my 7 year old appreciated the beauty of the house itself and the uniqueness of the entire property!   Very well done, we will be back to celebrate something else soon!

data.title: Great Lunch
data.text:
Excellent lunch for our large group. 
Love this place! Sure to please! Always great food and service in this unique historic house. It's a must try in St. Joseph.

data.title: Amazing amazing amazingly good!
data.text: This restaurant has it all - ambiance, hometown beautiful, eclectic - and most of all - great hosts and service and the food, OMGoodness amazing!  Be sure and make reservations and you won't be disappointed.  It's fabulous for women's gatherings and you will leave feeling very special.

data.title: Best fine dining in St. Joseph!
data.text: Top-tier New York chef Jeff presents a meal that is original and delicious, very substantial, and beautifully presented.  Ambiance and service are impeccable.  Outstanding from start to finish!

data.title: Exquisite Meal
data.text: This restaurant is very special. You must do advance reservations as well as entree choice. They have a limited menu that is outstanding! Our party chose lamb  or filet although other items were available. You receive three courses all of which are to be savored and enjoyed with each bite. If you want alcoholic beverages, you must bring your own. We brought wine and the gracious restaurant hosts were happy to uncork and pour for us. The trio of desserts served were scrumptious!  The beautiful Victorian home was a wondrous setting for this incredible meal! Enjoy!!!

data.title: What a treat!
data.text: Wonderful food, GREAT owners!  Make a reservation now!  Lunch from set menu includes entree and desert.  Able to meet special dietary needs.

data.title: Excellent Food and Amazing Service
data.text: We have enjoyed every visit to the JC Wyatt House.  We were served gourmet food and treated as special guests.  We also chose the restaurant to have our daughter's bridal luncheon.  We had the whole room to ourselves.  It will give you a taste of old St. Joe.  It is a great venue for special events like an anniversary or milestone birthday.  You will choose from a specified menu when you call for reservations, but I guarantee you will like everything that is served.  We did not go away hungry.

data.title: Wonderful place.  Period
data.text: I went with a group of friends for lunch.  Wyatt House is available by reservation only, and your order needs to be placed with your reservation.  We were met by the owner / server, seated promptly and our beautifully plated meals were served almost immediately.  We each enjoyed our entree, and were delighted to find a trio of small desserts was included with the meal.  Coffee was wonderful, too.  Plan a meal at this wonderful establishment, and talk with the owner to get a rich history of the restoration of this Victorian-era home.  I plan to return!
